subSubSection.paragraph:
Male epiproct.
Epiproct dorsallimb usually apically truncate, and bearing a prominent, suture in apical half of limb (
Fig. 46
); apical section of limb bears numerous fine anastomosed grooves and ridges covering apicalhalf (
Fig. 48
); basally the wide, apical, ridged section is separated from smooth and narrowed base by a pair of lateral concavities (
Figs. 46‐47
). Lower limb slightly widerthan upperlimbfor most of length and bearing subapical notches.
